draw((0,0,0)--(0,0,1), red);
draw((0,1,0)--(0,1,1), green);
draw((1,1,0)--(1,1,1), green);
draw((1,0,0)--(1,0,1), green);
draw((0,1,1)--(0,0,1)--(1,0,1), blue);
draw((1,0,1)--(1,1,1)--(0,1,1));
</asy>

This means that the probability that a randomly-selected pair of edges determine a plane is <math>\frac{7}{11}</math>, and we calculate that there are <math>{12 \choose 2} = 66</math> total pairs of edges that could be chosen (without the restriction). Thus the answer is <math>\frac{7}{11} \cdot 66 =\boxed{\textbf{(D) }42}</math>.

